Problems with Vuex:

Boilerplate-heavy

Mutations concept confusing

Weak TypeScript support

Verbose patterns

Pinia advantages:

✔ No mutations
✔ Direct state modification
✔ Better TypeScript inference
✔ Modular by default
✔ Composition API friendly

👉 Interview one-liner:

Pinia simplifies Vuex by removing mutations and embracing Composition API patterns.

3️⃣ Core Concepts of Pinia

Every Pinia store has:

State → data

Getters → derived state

Actions → business logic

defineStore('user', {
  state: () => ({ user: null }),
  getters: {},
  actions: {}
})

4️⃣ defineStore() — Two Ways
1️⃣ Options Store (Vuex-like)
export const useUserStore = defineStore('user', {
  state: () => ({
    user: null
  }),
  getters: {
    isLoggedIn: (state) => !!state.user
  },
  actions: {
    logout() {
      this.user = null
    }
  }
})


✔ Familiar
✔ Easy migration from Vuex

2️⃣ Setup Store (Composition API Style 🔥)
export const useUserStore = defineStore('user', () => {
  const user = ref(null)
  const isLoggedIn = computed(() => !!user.value)

  function logout() {
    user.value = null
  }

  return { user, isLoggedIn, logout }
})




✔ More flexible
✔ Best for complex logic
✔ Ideal for seniors

5️⃣ Using Pinia in Components
const userStore = useUserStore()


State:

userStore.user


Actions:

userStore.logout()


Getters:

userStore.isLoggedIn

6️⃣ Reactivity Rules (VERY IMPORTANT)
Destructuring pitfall ❌
const { user } = useUserStore() // breaks reactivity

Correct way ✔
const store = useUserStore()
const { user } = storeToRefs(store)


👉 Interviewers love this question.

7️⃣ Actions — Async & Sync
Async action example
actions: {
  async fetchUser() {
    this.user = await api.getUser()
  }
}


✔ No need for mutations
✔ Actions can call other actions

8️⃣ Getters — Computed Under the Hood
getters: {
  fullName: (state) => state.first + ' ' + state.last
}


Key points:

Cached

Reactive

Cannot be async

9️⃣ Cross-Store Communication
const authStore = useAuthStore()


Used inside another store’s action.

✔ Allowed
✔ Clean
❌ Avoid circular dependencies

🔟 Store Subscriptions (Advanced)
Subscribe to state changes
store.$subscribe((mutation, state) => {
  console.log(state)
})


Use cases:
✔ Logging
✔ Analytics
✔ Persistence

1️⃣1️⃣ Store Persistence (Real World)
pinia.use(({ store }) => {
  store.$subscribe((_, state) => {
    localStorage.setItem(store.$id, JSON.stringify(state))
  })
})


✔ User session
✔ Theme preferences

⚠️ Don’t persist sensitive data blindly.

